         <abstract>
            <p>This paper is devoted to the presentation and the analysis of a new particle method for convection-diffusion equations. The method has been presented in detail in the first part of this paper for an isotropic diffusion operator. This part is concerned with the extension of the method to anisotropic diffusion operators. The consistency and the accuracy of the method require much more complex conditions on the cutoff functions than in the isotropic case. After detailing these conditions, we give several examples of cutoff functions which can be used for practical computations. A detailed error analysis is then performed.</p>
          </abstract>
